			<div class="article-correspondence layout-item fill-pattern-light">
		<div class="layout-item-intro">
			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="2980">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>I&rsquo;ve been reading your magazine in bits and pieces for three or four months now. The August issue finally did it. Gregg Levoy&rsquo;s &ldquo;<a href="/article/1513">Off the Map</a>&rdquo; thrilled and delighted me. The first thing that got me was the quote from Rilke: &ldquo;The purpose of life is to be defeated by greater and greater things.&rdquo; The very same epiphany had occurred to me in the shower that morning.</p>

<p>Next came the part about surrender being something that midlife excels at teaching. It was almost as if the guy had been in the shower with me.</p>

<p>I knew I was going to subscribe when I got to the bottom of the second page and read, &ldquo;That clump of feathers was still stuck to my office window like a suicide note.&rdquo; I don&rsquo;t know who Levoy is, but I&rsquo;d love him for a pen pal.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Necia<br>Fulton, California</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

								<div class="block-correspondence" id="2948">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>Reading your November issue, I tried to reconcile the quote from Rilke in the <a href="/issues/227/correspondence">Correspondence</a> section &mdash; &ldquo;The purpose of life is to be defeated by greater and greater things&rdquo; &mdash; and the <a href="/article/6055">Sunbeam</a> from Simone Weil: &ldquo;The only way into truth is through one&rsquo;s own annihilation; through dwelling a long time in a state of extreme and total humiliation.&rdquo;</p>

<p>Am I to conclude that humiliation and defeat are the sperm and egg of joy?</p>

<p>I stand bemused by it all.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Jerry Medlock<br>Buckner, Arkansas</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

				<div class="text-center">
			<button class="b b-1 xsmall js-b-readmore-correspondence" data-collapsible="#article-correspondences" data-label="Read More Letters">Read More Letters</button>
		</div>
			</div>
    
		<div class="article-correspondence-cta">
		<div class="cta cta-l1" data-url="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">
			<div class="cta-intro">
				<h5 class="cta-title alt-ff">Thinking about writing us a letter?</h5>
				<p class="cta-text">Give in to the temptation. We love getting mail. <br><span class="xsmall">(Of course, we reserve the right to edit.)</span></p>
			</div>
			<a href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor" class="cta-button b b-4 b-padding-tight small" data-label="Write Us A Letter!">Write Us A Letter!</a>
		</div>
	</div>
	

